<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A file system that allows overlaying one \\p AbstractFileSystem on top</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of another.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Consists of a stack of &gt;=1 \\p FileSystem objects, which are treated as being</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><Highlight kind="comment">/// one merged file system. When there is a directory that exists in more than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><Highlight kind="comment">/// one file system, the \\p OverlayFileSystem contains a directory containing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the union of their contents.  The attributes (permissions, etc.) of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><Highlight kind="comment">/// top-most (most recently added) directory are used.  When there is a file</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that exists in more than one file system, the file in the top-most file</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><Highlight kind="comment">/// system overrides the other(s).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/overlayfilesystem"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/overlayfilesystem/#a63c09bb7eb0cfdb6de7bcddbaed4fb56">OverlayFileSystem</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/rttiextends">RTTIExtends</a>&lt;OverlayFileSystem, FileSystem&gt; &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Add a hard link to a file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Here hard links are not intended to be fully equivalent to the classical</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// filesystem. Both the hard link and the file share the same buffer and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// status (and thus have the same UniqueID). Because of this there is no way</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The \\p Target path must be an existing file or a hardlink. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p NewLink file must not have been added before. The \\p Target</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// path must not be a directory. The \\p NewLink node is added as a hard</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// link which points to the resolved file of \\p Target node.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystemparser">RedirectingFileSystemParser</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A virtual file system parsed from a YAML file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Currently, this class allows creating virtual files and directories. Virtual</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><Highlight kind="comment">/// files map to existing external files in \\c ExternalFS, and virtual</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directories may either map to existing directories in \\c ExternalFS or list</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><Highlight kind="comment">/// their contents in the form of other virtual directories and/or files.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The basic structure of the parsed file is:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\verbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;version&#39;: &lt;version number&gt;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &lt;optional configuration&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;roots&#39;: &#91;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><Highlight kind="comment">///              &lt;directory entries&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><Highlight kind="comment">///            &#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endverbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The roots may be absolute or relative. If relative they will be made</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><Highlight kind="comment">/// absolute against either current working directory or the directory where</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the Overlay YAML file is located, depending on the &#39;root-relative&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><Highlight kind="comment">/// configuration.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><Highlight kind="comment">/// All configuration options are optional.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;case-sensitive&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=(true for Posix, false for Windows)&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;use-external-names&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=true&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;root-relative&#39;: &lt;string, one of &#39;cwd&#39; or &#39;overlay-dir&#39;, default=&#39;cwd&#39;&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;overlay-relative&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=false&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;fallthrough&#39;: &lt;boolean, default=true, deprecated - use &#39;redirecting-with&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><Highlight kind="comment">///                   instead&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;redirecting-with&#39;: &lt;string, one of &#39;fallthrough&#39;, &#39;fallback&#39;, or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><Highlight kind="comment">///                        &#39;redirect-only&#39;, default=&#39;fallthrough&#39;&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><Highlight kind="comment">/// To clarify, &#39;root-relative&#39; option will prepend the current working</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directory, or the overlay directory to the &#39;roots-&gt;name&#39; field only if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#39;roots-&gt;name&#39; is a relative path. On the other hand, when &#39;overlay-relative&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is set to &#39;true&#39;, external paths will always be prepended with the overlay</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directory, even if external paths are not relative paths. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#39;root-relative&#39; option has no interaction with the &#39;overlay-relative&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><Highlight kind="comment">/// option.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Virtual directories that list their contents are represented as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\verbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;directory&#39;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;contents&#39;: &#91; &lt;file or directory entries&gt; &#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endverbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The default attributes for such virtual directories are:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\verbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MTime = now() when created</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Perms = 777</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><Highlight kind="comment">/// User = Group = 0</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Size = 0</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><Highlight kind="comment">/// UniqueID = unspecified unique value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endverbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When a path prefix matches such a directory, the next component in the path</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is matched against the entries in the &#39;contents&#39; array.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Re-mapped directories, on the other hand, are represented as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><Highlight kind="comment">/// /// \\verbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;directory-remap&#39;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;use-external-name&#39;: &lt;boolean&gt;, # Optional</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;external-contents&#39;: &lt;path to external directory&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endverbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><Highlight kind="comment">/// and inherit their attributes from the external directory. When a path</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><Highlight kind="comment">/// prefix matches such an entry, the unmatched components are appended to the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#39;external-contents&#39; path, and the resulting path is looked up in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><Highlight kind="comment">/// external file system instead.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Re-mapped files are represented as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\verbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;type&#39;: &#39;file&#39;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;name&#39;: &lt;string&gt;,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;use-external-name&#39;: &lt;boolean&gt;, # Optional</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#39;external-contents&#39;: &lt;path to external file&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endverbatim</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Their attributes and file contents are determined by looking up the file at</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><Highlight kind="comment">/// their &#39;external-contents&#39; path in the external file system.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For &#39;file&#39;, &#39;directory&#39; and &#39;directory-remap&#39; entries the &#39;name&#39; field may</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><Highlight kind="comment">/// contain multiple path components (e.g. /path/to/file). However, any</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="comment">/// directory in such a path that contains more than one child must be uniquely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><Highlight kind="comment">/// represented by a &#39;directory&#39; entry.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When the &#39;use-external-name&#39; field is set, calls to \\a vfs::File::status()</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><Highlight kind="comment">/// give the external (remapped) filesystem name instead of the name the file</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><Highlight kind="comment">/// was accessed by. This is an intentional leak through the \\a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><Highlight kind="comment">/// RedirectingFileSystem abstraction layer. It enables clients to discover</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><Highlight kind="comment">/// (and use) the external file location when communicating with users or tools</Highlight></CodeLine>
